        >>> r = R.from_matrix([[0, -1, 0],
        ...                    [1, 0, 0],
        ...                    [0, 0, 1]])
        >>> r.as_quat()
        array([0.        , 0.        , 0.70710678, 0.70710678])
        >>> r.as_quat().shape
        (4,)

        Represent a stack with a single rotation:

        >>> r = R.from_quat([[0, 0, 0, 1]])
        >>> r.as_quat().shape
        (1, 4)

        Represent multiple rotations in a single object:

        >>> r = R.from_rotvec([[np.pi, 0, 0], [0, 0, np.pi/2]])
        >>> r.as_quat().shape
        (2, 4)

